{"key":"post-13361323","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13361323</id>\n<content>As said, wait until your grains are fully 100% colonized.&amp;nbsp; Use roughly a 1:10 ratio of spawn to straw(using your eyeballs-don't measure) and colonize the straw log on a shelf in an open room at normal room temperature.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At fruiting, simply mist to maintain substrate moisture content as needed, and run a small humidifier if a greenhouse is used, or perlite if a terrarium is used.&amp;nbsp; If using a shotgun terrarium, leave the lid off or at least not sealed well for extra fresh air.&amp;nbsp; Straw logs put out a lot of CO2 and this has to be dissipated to get good fruiting performance.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13361432</next>\n<prev>13361305</prev>\n<first>13243061</first>\n<last>13485564</last>\n<when>1287589512</when>\n<utime>10/20/10 06:45 PM</utime>\n</post>"}